			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			Ok first of all it's a little wrong in how it works and i'll get the fix applied ASAP. But you might as well know how it works before and after the fix.<br />
<br />
Right now this it currently works like this. When a player loses 75% or more of their planets within a 24 hour period they get empire protection (they cannot be sieged) for 12 hours. They can still be opped, raided, privateered, and blockaded. If said player sieges, blockades, raids, privateers, or performs special operations within those 12 hours they lose protection. They are still free to do anything else though. Ok the 'bug' right now though, is that only planets lost when there are NO DEFENDING FLEETS count. so if you hit 4 planets and don't want to die, station your fleets on your home planet and when they take 3 planets, you'll be knocked into pmode.<br />
<br />
basically as soon as the patch is applied it'll count planet losses in all cases, not just when you have no fleets defending.<br />
<br />
NOTE: it is possible to lose the protection within those 12 hours. if AS gets rebooted for say, an update. it whipes the protection status (it doesn't save). basically this is just a measure to help noobies, but don't feel falsely secure from it						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
